obs_notes: Surveys were designed to be rapid searches for a number of species, so counts of species and the life stages were taken for the entire reach. UTMs of positive observations were not recorded. Sedge and herbaceous vegetation. Southern area of wetland consistently has water from main pool downward; this stretch may be permanent, but the two northern arms may be dry by the end of the summer. Northern two arms have very dry braids under dense vegetation so may have been inundated in the past but seems to have been dry for years or floods for a short period of time seasonally because beds are dusty. Northeast spring is located in campground where it is fenced and drained into the spring via piping. Bury described a marshy area with pools with the campground as its southern border, this area was scouted and found to be dry. Saw a skink of unknown species. End water temp missing, may be due to dry area at end of site.
